    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="481"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13329/1–3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Emperor of Japan</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American people are deeply grieved and shocked at the terrible naval disaster
                    which has just caused the loss of the lives of so many <pb facs="0608" n="506"
                        xml:id="pg_506"/> gallant officers and men of the Japanese Navy. On their
                    behalf and personally on my own account I desire to express my profound sympathy
                    and concern, and I wish it were in my power to show this sympathy in more
                    practical fashion than by mere words.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Roosevelt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
